| peer-reviewed = | language = | editor = Keith Eggener | publisher = University of California | country = | history = 1941–present | frequency = Quarterly | openaccess = | license = | impact = | impact-year = | ISSNlabel = | ISSN = 0037-9808 | eISSN = 2150-5926 | CODEN = | JSTOR = | LCCN = | OCLC = | website = http://www.sah.org/publications-and-research/jsah | link1 = | link1-name = | link2 = <!-- up to |link5= --> | link2-name = <!-- up to |link5-name= --> | boxwidth = }}
The '''''Journal of the Society of Architectural Historians''''' ({{ISSN|0037-9808}}) is a quarterly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[academic journal]] published by the [[University of California Press]] on behalf of the [[Society of Architectural Historians]].<ref>{{cite web |title= Journal Info |url= https://www.jstor.org/journal/jsociarchhist |work= Journal of the Society of Architectural Historians |agency= JSTOR.org |accessdate= 26 September 2012}}</ref> It was established in 1941 as the '''''Journal of the American Society of Architectural Historians''''', and was renamed to its current title in the post-World War II period, around 1945. The founding [[editor-in-chief]] was [[Turpin Bannister]].<ref>{{cite journal |last= Howland |first= Richard H. |title=In Memoriam Turpin Chambers Bannister 1904-1982 |journal= Journal of the Society of Architectural Historians |date=Dec 1982 |volume=41 |issue=4 |pages= 279–280 |doi= 10.2307/989799 |jstor= 989799}}</ref> The current editor is Keith Eggener, architectural history professor at the University of Oregon. The journal's issues include scholarly articles on international topics in architectural history, [[book review]]s, architectural exhibition reviews, field notes, and editorials on the relationship between the built environment, its study, and interdisciplinary topics.<ref>{{cite web |url= http://www.sah.org/publications-and-research/jsah |title= Journal of the Society of Architectural Historians |publisher= Society of Architectural Historians |work= |accessdate= November 26, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |url= https://books.google.com/books?id=Zq9bB__W5tMC&pg=PA24&dq=Society+of+Architectural+Historians&hl=en&sa=X&ei=x-lmUpCyEMGyyAGc7oC4Aw&ved=0CE4Q6AEwBjgU#v=onepage&q=Society%20of%20Architectural%20Historians&f=false| title=Writing Spaces: Discourses of Architecture, Urbanism and the Built Environment, 1960-2000 | publisher=[[Routledge]] | author=Crysler, C. Greig | year=2003 |location=New York | pages=24 | isbn=0203402685}}</ref>
